  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large, bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to one side of a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and the <strong>dried oregano</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an in initial 20 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688482562795-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688482562795-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688482562795-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688482562795-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1688482562795-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, peel and chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Trim the <strong>green beans</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>green beans</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) to a large piece of <strong>tin foil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, then scrunch the foil around the green beans to form a tightly sealed parcel</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Make 2 parcels!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688482567797-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688482567797-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688482567797-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688482567797-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1688482567797-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>After the initial 15 min, remove the tray from the oven and add the <strong>green bean parcel</strong> to the other side of the tray</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p><p>Return the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> to the oven for 10-12 min further or until the green beans are tender – these are your <strong>crispy oregano potatoes & garlic green beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688482574625-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688482574625-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688482574625-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688482574625-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1688482574625-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>remaining chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!) and <strong>mayo </strong>in a small bowl with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>balsamic sun-dried tomato paste </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!), a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> (you’ll use the rest later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>tangy mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688482586185-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688482586185-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688482586185-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688482586185-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1688482586185-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cornflour</strong> and 30g <span class=\"text-danger\">[60g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to a shallow dish with the <strong>remaining balsamic sun-dried tomato paste</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika </strong>and the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> remaining white wine vinegar </strong>and 70ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[140ml] </span><strong>very cold water </strong>and whisk everything together until there are no lumps – this is your <strong>batter</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1688482592065-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
